{"about_the_game":"<img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2299740/extras/TextGif4.gif?t=1728689915\" /><br><br>In lush alpine mountains and meadows stands the renowned equestrian capital of Europe, a town called <strong>Rein Ravine</strong> and its surrounding province of the same name.<br><br>You have been admitted to study in its highly sought-after Rein Ravine <strong>Equine University International</strong>, alongside with other ambitious equestrians from around the world. This once in a lifetime opportunity leads you to train in the three most common European disciplines - showjumping, dressage, and cross country - under the eye of masters claimed to be some of the best in the world. But is equestrian life in this prestigious village as glamorous as it appears?<br><br>The Early Access version of Tales of Rein Ravine doesn't contain the storyline yet, but while waiting for the school year to begin, you can visit the barns in Rein Ravine and take summer riding lessons!<br><br><br><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2299740/extras/TextImage3.png?t=1728689915\" /><br><br><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2299740/extras/TextGif3.gif?t=1728689915\" /><br><br><br>Tales of Rein Ravine aims to challenge its players with <strong>first-of-its-kind riding mechanics and gameplay</strong> heavily inspired by real-life horse riding, as well as tell an intriguing story - more mature than typical in its genre - to a young adult audience of horse gamers. Horses in Rein Ravine are versatile to ride, ranging from calm and experienced geldings to hot-blooded mares and easily spooked young stallions. <br><br><br><br><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2299740/extras/TextImage1.png?t=1728689915\" />","background":"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/s